SSH SESSION
1. find the ip adress using the cmd <ip a> in debian os.
2. find the username using <echo $USER> cmd.
3. run the cmd:
	ssh username@ip_adress

Graphic Session
1. make sure that "X11forwarding" is set to "yes" on the path
	/etc/ssh/sshd_config, else set it on the active mode "yes" also 
	if the line is commented make sure to uncomment it by removing 
    the hashtag.
2. find the ip adress and the username using the same commands.
3. run the following cmd:
	ssh -X username@ip_adress
